01/05/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- Police seized some 320kg of marijuana as part of a weekend operation dubbed "Wet Road", according to a statement issued on Sunday (30 April). 
Officials say the drugs were found in cars on the Vlora-Fier road. 
Three Albanian citizens were arrested. 
They are believed to be part of a wider drug trafficking network.
In Croatia, the Agency for the Suppression of Corruption and Organised Crime announced on Friday that a human and drugs trafficking ring was smashed in an operation conducted jointly by Croatian, Italian and Slovenian police authorities. 
A dozen people were arrested in the three countries. 
(Albanian News - 01/05/06; HRT - 28/04/06)
